It is pretty cold outside, so if you are looking for something delicious to enjoy as you snuggle up during the weekend, this recipe is for you. Mocha coffee is easy to make, you only need a microwave or just a stovetop. It can be made iced or hot. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 In a small pot or microwave-safe cup, stir together sugar, cocoa powder, and water. Step 2 Microwave it for 30 seconds, then stir. Ensure the sugar and cocoa powder are dissolved completely. Step 3 Stir in coffee and milk and continue to heat until it steams for 1 minute. Whisk the mixture vigorously until it foams, then top up with whipped cream. Enjoy!